title: Precise and controllable Live Bacteria Therapeutics (LBTs)
description:
img: /assets/img/fig-engineered.png
importance: 2
category: ongoing
---

The human body is host to diverse microbial communities, and the complex interactions
between the host and its microbial counterparts play a key role in human health and
disease. How to utilize complex interactions between microbial communities and hosts
to treat diseases, such as inflammation and tumor, become a new therapeutic strategy. 
The idea of Live Bacteria Therapeutics (LBTs) is to engineer bacterial chassis to produce therapeutics that
are able to repair or restore healthy microbial function and diversity. Existing efforts have primarily focused 
on engineering probiotic bacterial strains from the Bacteroides or Lactobacillus families or Escherichia coli from labs.
One challenge of using engineered probiotics as the next genereation therapy is to realize precise diagnosis and
controllable treatment. Therefore, engineered protbiotics should sense inflammation region or pathogens and only release
certain amount of drugs, and induce exiting or self-killing mechanisms for biocontainment.


