We are intereted in one highly harmful pathogen, Helicobacter pylori (h. pylori), which directly leads to stomach cancer. The pathogen
h. pylori can survive the acidic environment and implant in human stomach and release toxins that induce severe diseaese. Traditional treatment
uses antibiotics for h. pylori eradication, yet it becomes less efficient due to the resistence of h. pylori and causes dysbiosis of the gut microbiota.
Therefore, we are looking for engineered probiotics that are specifically designed to eradicate h. pylori while not interfering with other healthy
microbiome. To realize precise and controllable treatment, we need to design feedback control circuit in probiotics that can sense the existence of
h. pylori, decide if certain amount of drugs need to be released, and check the therapeutics effect and turn on exiting or self-killing procedure.
